Regional Market Insights
North America: Dominates the global market, a position solidified by widespread consumer adoption of gluten-free diets not just for medical reasons but as a lifestyle choice.
Europe: Represents a mature and highly regulated market, where EU-wide gluten-free labeling standards (requiring less than 20 ppm gluten) have built significant consumer trust and market stability.
Asia-Pacific & Latin America: These are dynamic emerging markets characterized by large, untapped consumer bases, growing middle-class disposable income, and increasing diagnostic capabilities for gluten-related disorders.
Middle East & Africa: While currently a smaller market, it exhibits positive growth indicators driven by urbanization, rising health consciousness, and the gradual entry of international brands.

